@startuml sequence_request_pipeline
!theme plain

title Request Pipeline - Full Middleware Chain

actor Client
participant "CORS\nMiddleware" as CORS
participant "Security\nHeaders" as Headers
participant "Rate Limit\nMiddleware" as RateLimit
participant "CSRF\nMiddleware" as CSRF
participant "Auth\nMiddleware" as Auth
participant "Validation\nMiddleware" as Validation
participant "Controller" as Controller
database "Redis" as Redis
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Client -> CORS : PATCH /api/v1/skills/{id}\nOrigin: https://skills.example.com\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt>\nX-CSRF-Token: <token>

CORS -> CORS : Check Origin\nagainst allowlist
CORS -> Headers : next()

Headers -> Headers : Queue HSTS, CSP,\nX-Frame-Options headers
Headers -> RateLimit : next()

RateLimit -> Redis : ZREMRANGEBYSCORE + ZCARD\n(sliding window check)
Redis --> RateLimit : count: 42
RateLimit -> RateLimit : 42 < 100, allowed.\nSet X-RateLimit headers.
RateLimit -> CSRF : next()

CSRF -> Redis : GET csrf:{token}
Redis --> CSRF : valid (user_id match)
CSRF -> Redis : DEL csrf:{token}\n(single-use)
CSRF -> Auth : next()

Auth -> Auth : Validate JWT signature\nand expiration.\nExtract user context.
Auth -> Validation : next()

Validation -> Validation : Schema validate body.\nStrip unknown fields.\nSanitize HTML.
Validation -> Controller : next()

Controller -> DB : UPDATE skills SET ...\nWHERE id = $1
DB --> Controller : Updated row
Controller --> Client : 200 OK\n+ Security headers\n+ Rate limit headers\n+ Updated resource JSON

@enduml
